caption: Best crepes since I was in Paris 30+ years ago, and nice people.
Great small business with wonderful people running it. Food was fantastic!
A unique little spot, tucked away on a side street. A real family feeling place with very good TEA.  Yes tea,  it goes so well with the Crepes.  We will be back on our next visit to Ia City.
Really sweet family, flexible vegetarian options, and delicious crepes!
HOMEMADE ice cream! Need I say more? Very fresh ingredients, friendly service, clean environment and unique, yet appetizing menu!
Ocean crepe is the best guys. Such nice people, nice atmosphere, i love this place !
Great food and service very good overall
Had some of the best Crepes I have ever had! Good atmosphere and nice owner.

If you're reading this because you're from out of town and looking for a close place too eat like I was. GO HERE! the people were so nice and helpful and the food is delicious. I ordered the Roma and it was off the charts. If you're looking for a good vibe, good food, good price kind of place look no further!
Very hospitable place. Owners are very friendly. Coffee is heavenly. Food is delicious. A bit crowded, though.
If you are looking the best crepes around, this is your spot. A few staff forgot the memo about wearing masks apparently but the service and food is good.
BY FAR MY FAVORITE RESTURANT TO EAT AT IN ALL OF JOHNSON COUNTY!!!!!! The owners are also so kind hearted and amazing people!!! I will forever go to crepes while I live in this area!!!
Amazing warm place and the owner is soo friendly, great food quality. Worth it to visit I drive one hour to eat there
Crepes were delicious 😋 atmosphere was great too and excellent service
Yum
Incredible! Owners are the best.
Some of the best crepes I’ve had.

Small family owned crepe restaurant that has savory and sweet crepes. Also breakfast crepes. Tried 3 different ones. All fantastic. The owners were awesome and super nice. Would recommend to any dnd all looking for authentic crepes and to support small businesses
I liked the crepes and the Moroccan tea, the service is excellent
I go here all the time now and get something different every time and it never fails to impress me. You will always enjoy this great, family friendly restaurant
Delicious food and great hostility

THIS  place is amazing! The food was so good and the prices are super affordable.  We fed our family .  We also appreciated the vegan/vegetarian menu.  All of us ate every bite.  The food was full of flavor and tasted fresh.  The staff was very friendly when we picked up our food.
Fun spot.  Driving  west on I80.  Wanted to find a cool local spot, and this popped up in our search.   Excellent food!   Great staff.   We will be back
great place to eat always
(Translated by Google) Delicious 😋  (Original) Delicioso 😋

Literally every dish I've sampled (Chirbuli, Rotisserie Chicken, buttered radishes, egg plant, Turkish peppers, okra, and wild mushroom)  has been excellent.  The atmosphere is great too.  There is no other place like this in KC.  I will be back with family, co-workers, and friends.

Everyone loved the food and atmosphere. Funny, they all live locally and had not been there. I had tuna and salmon rigging - admittedly cautious vshome, it was stellar!!! I also had a house salad - if you like oldfashioned,homemade blue cheese dressing, this is the place. My guests had a variety of sandwiches - all loved their meals. Well done and we'll be back

The employees are some of the sweetest people I’ve ever met. They always take great care to truly make you feel valued as a customer and a person. They have both savory and sweet crepes, and have the option to use a gluten free batter!  The prices are very affordable too. One crepe is usually enough to be full, but buying two won’t break the bank either. The atmosphere is amazing - between the decor, music, and cozy layout, it truly feels like a cafe from a movie!
Food was delicious, environment was amazing, waitresses were quick, friendly and attentive. A must try!
Wonderful! Reminded me of being in Paris
Great tasting food. Fresh ingredients.
Perfect.
Great service and even better food!!
Delicious crepes, my family loves them.
I would recommend this to anyone looking for some great food and even better service!! I Definitely plan on eating here again.
The perfect place to be for a Cafe and some crepes!!! Love 💘 😻
Very delicious food. Crepes lover dream
Lovely owners and amazing food. Must try if you are in Iowa City.  With both savory and sweet options, you can find your daily mood in a plate.
Amazing food, great service, kind staff. Black owned business.
Black owned business. Great food and great service. 👍

Best crepes in Iowa City, Maybe in all of Iowa! They not only taste fantastic, they also LOOKS GREAT! (Sorry, I don’t have any pics) I went here with my Dad and it was de-lish. The kids working were very polite and communicative to use, answered all our questions about the town and university. Keep up the great work!
reminds me of my time in southern france
Great food and amazing coffee 💕💕
We went the sweet and savory route and were floored!! They were both so incredibly delicious! Can't wait to order again soon.
LOVE the crepes!  SO GOOD!  And also love the family that owns this business.  Couldn't be nicer people!
Amazing food.. for what I believe to be a very cheap price!
Very savory crepes. Fast and great service.
Absolutely fantastic!!
Yet another delightful experience from Hicham and crew! Exquisitely tasty food and delightfully gracious people.
Delicious, rich flavors and relatively fast alternative to the usual heavy downtown lunch and dinner options.
Great crepes at a reasonable price.

Delicious food. I ordered two plates for myself.  The ratatouille and the Du Bal. The latter is sweetened with rum raisins and bananas. Very tasty and hand made with pride unlike the franchise breakfast restaurants.  This place is small but the customer service is second to none.
Delicious and beautiful crepes!
Absolutely delicious food.
Love crepes! So friendly. I've tried a majority of the menu. Haven't disliked anything.
Fantastic crêpes and the owner is so nice!
Fantastic! I have never had a crepe before I went here and it was great
I cannot get enough of this place. Share a savory and a sweet in this intimate little cafe.
Great food, I've loved this place since I was a child.
Love this place!  Try them for sure!
The food was beautifully made and absolutely delicious . Owners are charming!
Amazing crepes and extraordinary service! You get the best of both worlds with savory and sweet. Try some homemade dessert and visit with the lovely staff!
Delicious! The environment is very cozy ad there are many options on the menu.
Great service. Loved that there was a gluten free option.
Actually delicious dont listen to the weird old guy on the ceiling
Affordable gourmet
Really delicious! Went here while visiting Iowa, and it's certainly worth checking out.

with a intimate, cozy atmosphere, nice staff, and crêpes both savory and sweet, this place is a go-to choice when you can’t decide what to eat. each crêpe ranges from $7-8. there’s a buy one get one half off deal tuesdays through thursdays. one crêpe will probably satisfy a fairly hungry adult. la rêve is the best.
Love the food!
We love extra salmon on our Ocean crepes!
I just like it.
Good food, good service
Crepes are tiny and over priced. Service is terrible. All three orders were screwed up. I could have made 20 at home for the price of one and it would've taken less time.
Great place for an intimate lunch with friends. The little girl with a big heart behind the counter makes it an amazing experience.
Wonder atmosphere and absolutely delicious food!
Excellent, as always!
Love the crepes

This restaurant deserves 5 stars because there is nothing like it in the area. This local restaurant serves wonderful crepes both savory and sweet. My only complaint is that they seem to always be close when I am craving one of their crepes!
Excellent crepes!
Its small and easy to miss but I really enjoyed the place. The Paris Crepe I had was really good (I like sweet things) and my friend who had the ratatouille (savory) enjoyes their meal.
Excellent crepes!
Love this place! Sweet and savory choices. Great service.
Awesome place, delightful crepes!

Everything about this place I loved! I don't think there is one thing on the menu that I wouldn't like. We shared both le cochon and crepe du chef. Spectaculor flavor! The owners are so nice and helpful. The place was clean and decor fit very nicely. I can't wait to go back. I'll be recommending this to all my friends/family. Thank you for such a refreshing experience.
Great food and service! Was pleasantly surprised
Great place..!

This is one of the best restaurants in Iowa City.  Their crepes are wonderful (the Roma is my favorite, with chicken, feta, and cranberries) and their gluten free chocolate cake is to die for, not too sweet with hints of orange in the frosting.
Beautiful flavors and color, very well done
Absolutely fantastic! Excellent quality food, both in taste and presentation, the service is wonderful, and the atmosphere pleasant! I highly recommend to anyone wanting a savory or sweet treat!
I love their crêpes! Small and cozy restaurant with great chefs. Only wish they were open later!
I always go there.  I love it
Deliciouso
Great food! Highly recommend.
very good. the savory crepes are just as good as, if not better than, the sweet ones. prices a little high but understandable for the quality of food.
Delicious food and great service!
Super tasty.   Wonderful staff who interacted with us while they prepared our food.   Our family of 14 were all delighted.

Hidden Gem! First time visit, freezing cold couldn't find a decent dinner stopped just by chance. Greeted with a genuine welcome and genuine smile. This was the beginning of the best crepes dinner in my life! Small, low key great food, great atmosphere, delightful prices! Wow!
Great coffee!
Liked the food...tried several different kinds. Nice, friendly staff.
What a find, in a sea of college fast food restaurants, this place was great! Crepes were top notch, and I hear they’re upgrading the coffee equipment soon.
Meal was great as well as the service!

Excellent crêpes. Very much like the real deal. If you’ve been to Europe before, you’ll know what I’m talking about. I have been here several times since I found the place. Their menu is extensive and all the crêpes look fantastic. The Cochon one is to die for. I like to order it with buckwheat batter. I love their buckwheat batter!!!! But if you want to play it safe, you can never go wrong with Nutella, of course 😉 service is super nice and welcoming. The space is intimate. Highly recommend!!!!
Beautiful little locally owned shop, for sure recommended

A fantastic spot! We were visiting and absolutely loved our breakfast here. Many types of crepes too choose from, made where you can see and really delicious! And the crepes are the perfect breakfast size! One was plenty for each of us.
Great food, personal experience.

I had been meaning to come here for a while and finally stepped in.  I had the Moroccan mint tea, hot to drink and it was very nice.  I ordered the herbs chicken crêpe.  Just in case you are wondering, they do only serve crêpes.  You can get sweet or savory and almost all of them can be made gluten-free.  The one I ordered was thin, but big...bigger than my face big.  It was filled with delicious, fresh ingredients.  It had a nice pesto drizzle over the top.  My first reaction was to admire the presentation...and then to dig right in.  I look forward to visiting again and trying one of the sweet varieties.  This is a unique restaurant with only a few tables and I don't see why they aren't full all the time.
Delicious crepes, very kind personel.
A cozy and comfy place to have a Turkish / Moroccan / Paris themed Crips.
Art in the form of crepes. Delicious!
Wonderful food in an amazing atmosphere!! One of my favorite places to eat in Iowa City.
Delicious and quiet
Awesome place with amazing food.
Crazy delicious! Great for breakfast or lunch. Cozy atmosphere and friendly service.
Nice quiet delicious crepes
Awesome!
Very good Crepes and amazing ingredients and options.   The gluten free crepes are amazing!
Amazing food and atmosphere!
Excellent crepes. Vegetarian options. Great experience.

A really enjoyable little crepes place, the pricing isn’t heinously expensive for the portions and the whole environment is warm and friendly. Never thought a good crepe place would come to Iowa City until now

I adore this place. It's my go-to for a quiet, gentle celebration. Birthdays, graduation... For 2-4 people, it's perfect. I have brought more friends and family members here than anywhere else in town.  There are sweet and savory options, with a good variety of both - it's a specific vibe but it is done masterfully. :)
I've eaten here every time I'm in town.  Fantastic breakfast.  Light, affordable, fresh, and quick.  Service is always top notch.  If you like tea, try the moroccan mint.
Excellent food and charming atmosphere.
We love this place.

This is a cozy, small place with very delicious crepes. The crepes were good and home-made, and they have gluten free batter options. They are lacking in the coffee department, though- they have drip coffee that they offered to reheat for me. They would definitely benefit from barista service and a full equipped espresso machine.
This is honestly my favorite little place to come.
They are great. Their savory crepes are better than their sweet crepes, but try La Reve, if you can.

The staff here is great. They are very friendly and helpful. They get 5 stars on their own.  On our visit, my husband and I both ordered sweet crepes. One of which was pretty good and the other was just okay. It's not a place I will write off trying again (especially to try the savory crepes), but I also won't consider it a must eat place in Iowa City.
I have lived here for years and now that I have visited I now know that I have been missing out. The herb chicken was fantastic!!
I love Crepes de Luxe, it's quite literally one of my favorite restaurants I've ever been to.  Amazing crepes, both sweet and savory, at amazing prices.
Great food and great atmosphere, just gets a little slow when it's busy, but that means you know it's worth it!
Excellent selections.  Not a bad one on the menu.
Crepe wasn't mind blowing. Very unique spot though, and enjoyed the decor. I came when it was relatively empty though - and it felt weird because pretty much no one else was there..
The crepes and staff are always great. We make a point to eat here everytime we visit Iowa City.
always exactly what it should be
Nice variety of sweet and savory crepes. One crepe is not enough, though, which makes this more expensive than it should be for "self-serve" dining.
Awesome place. Good food choices
These crepes are sooo tasty! Awesome that they break their menu into two categories - savory and sweet. Really good place for not only dessert but for small meals.
I visit here all the time! I am gluten-free because of Celiac disease and you can watch them prepare your crepe. I've never once gotten sick and the crepes are delicious!
the crepes are light and delicious. I suggest L'Ocean to anyone who enjoys salmon and lemon.  Great place to relax and just enjoy the food!
Cannot describe in words the deliciousness that occurs there. You must experience it for yourself.
Good food, fun atmosphere. Wished they changed the menu every now and then though
Iowa city's most underrated restaurant
Impressive, multidimensional tastes. I Loved it, and so did my friends. I got the salmon. Yum! Service was quick and good.
Food was and is always incredible!!!
Amazing crepes, both sweet and savory. Weird hours, but totally worth it. Best crepes in Iowa hands down.
Really enjoy the food, especially since I can't get it normally.
Amazing place! Tons of choices for all the tastes! Everything was delicious! Highly recommend!!!

A friend recommended this place while I was visiting Iowa City and I absolutely adored it.  The staff was patient and helpful, and the crepes are absolutely delicious.  I had the Herb Chicken.  I was concerned about the quality of the chicken since the chicken was pre-cooked.  But it was absolutely delicious - high quality and moist.  And, of course I got a dessert crepe.
Love them crepes
crepes are delicious here, and the staff is full of lovely people!
We love this place. Top notch chef, menu has variety (in crepes) and they offer gluten free options.
Wonderfully nice couple runs the place. Their crêpes are tasty as well!
Delicious! A little taste of France right here in Iowa. Owners are delightful. Very cozy, about 4 tables.
Great food and great service. Perfect place for a date on Valentine's day. But make sure you have a reservation, they're busy that day!
Wonderful food. Small place and very friendly.
Absolutely excellent crepes, great service. A little low on tables for the crowd.
Crepes de Luxe was incredible. The food was delectable, the service was unparalleled, and the atmosphere was cozy.

I've been there twice now and both time fantastic, the atmosphere is quiet, service superb, you get to watch them make your crepe' and the flavors.  First time there everyone ordered their own thing, second time went with 2 friends ordered two savory and 1 desert, they split the orders 3 ways and we all got to enduldge.  New favorite place in IC....
Excellent food,  great service

I've never been here before, but I took a group of 5 people to Crepes de Luxe last night for dinner. I've had crepes before, so I kinda knew how good it would be. But I'm sorry... This was even better than any crepe place I've ever been to in Atlanta! I had one with Nutella, banana and raisins plus I tried the Roma. Both were fantastic! Price was low for the amount of work that is done on each crepe. Go... you can thank me later!
Very shiny atmosphere and their crepes are art!! Enjoy delicious and beautiful crepes~! :)
Food was a bit overpriced, but fine. Would give 3 stars, but the server was quite nice.

Outstanding in every respect.  Stopped there with two coworkers tonight and we all loved it.  The best word to describe my crepe was sophisticated.  I can't really think of what to compare it to as it was so unique yet so flavorful.  I loved how you could watch as your crepe was made.  And the plating when they present it to you was almost a work of art.  I didn't find the prices high at all.  This isn't fast food, and paying under $7 for food of this quality is a value to me.

Amazing new gem in Iowa City. Visited for lunch and we tried their Lyon, Ratatouille and Monkey.  All three were fantastic and the presentation wonderful.  They add a little artistic touch to each crepe and it's appreciated.  Endless coffee is a nice extra plus and all the staff is incredibly friendly and helpful.  Very cozy and hope they get to expand their menu a bit once they grow...fountain soda? small side salads (i love my veggies!)? espresso?
